      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change <2% between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated screw geometry (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 118k, fine: 310k). Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 1.8% for all three QoIs. Discretization error contribution to total uncertainty budget is 0.9%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria tightened to 1e-6; nonlinear iteration history reviewed for all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Implicit nonlinear solver with Newton-Raphson iteration; force and displacement residuals converged to 1e-7 at each load step. No divergence observed across 200 load increments. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in original build; documented checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by independent senior analyst using FDA simulation checklist (SOP-FEA-2021-003). Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material assignments confirmed correct. No use errors identified. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of constitutive model choice with literature support; simplifying assumptions documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, Et=2.2 GPa) selected based on published coupon data and ISO 5832-3. Contact modeled as frictional (μ=0.25) with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Geometric nonlinearity enabled. All assumptions documented in model description report MDR-2022-NC-001. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs sourced from traceable measurements; nominal values used in deterministic runs with UQ envelope quantified.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of 11 production screws (mean ± 1σ tolerances applied). Material properties from lot-specific tensile coupon testing (n=6 per lot). Monte Carlo UQ (n=10,000 samples) propagated all 14 uncertain inputs through the model. A screening sensitivity study described in the UQ narrative identified cortical modulus and screw-rod interface friction coefficient as likely dominant contributors to output variance; however, the formal ranking of input drivers was not encoded as a structured sensitivity analysis artifact within this credibility package. Gradation 3 achieved for model inputs given traceability and UQ coverage."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lots; geometric characterization of each specimen prior to testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled per ASTM F1717 protocol. Specimens drawn from three production lots. CMM measurement of each screw prior to assembly. Construct geometry documented in test report TR-2021-NC-F1717. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing at multiple load levels or boundary condition variants to bracket COU envelope; environmental conditions controlled and documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard setup, 10° offset block) at ambient temperature. Only one test condition explored; no variation in offset angle, load rate, or simulated bone quality. This limits the ability to confirm model validity across the COU envelope. Gradation 2 achieved; required level 3 not met. Identified as known gap in coverage but does not preclude acceptance given medium model risk and corroborating multi-laboratory agreement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to measured specimen parameters; documented mapping between experimental measurements and simulation inputs.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 simulations used specimen-specific CMM-measured geometry and lot-matched material properties. Friction coefficient estimated from tribological characterization of Ti-Ti interfaces reported in peer-reviewed literature (Niinomi 2002). Input mapping table provided in equivalency report EQR-2022-NC-001. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoIs; acceptance threshold pre-specified as E/uval < 1.96 and relative error <10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 9 for stiffness (1.12), yield force (1.44), and force at 40 mm (1.61). All three QoIs satisfy both the <1.96 E/uval threshold and the <10% relative error criterion. Comparison performed blind to simulation results prior to unblinding. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory decision; traceability to design requirements documented.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to construct mechanical integrity under physiological loading. Traceability to design requirement DR-2021-007 (minimum yield force 800 N) documented. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
