    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given: (1) multi-laboratory experimental confirmation reduces concern about single-condition testing, (2) model risk level 3 is addressed by the comprehensive UQ envelope (Monte Carlo, n=10,000), and (3) all three QoIs satisfy pre-specified E/uval and relative error thresholds. The credibility evidence package is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
